1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. Bd3 Nf6 7. O-O Nc6 8. Be3 h5 9. f4?? { Too ambitious and loses on the spot! This traps shows just how much pressure Black has in the center. 9. h3 is basically forced to not let Black have even the slightest advantage. } 9... Ng4 { Attack on the bishop, therefore the defense on the Nd4 will also be loosened. } 10. Qf3 (10. Nxc6 Nxe3 11. Qe2 Nxf1) 10... Nxe3 11. Qxe3 (11. Nxc6 Nxf1) 11... Nxd4 12. Qxd4 Bc5 { White's queen is pinned! } *


[Event "Sicilian Kan Repertoire: 5. Nc3 with 6. Be2"]
