1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. b3 a6 4. Bb2 b5 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 Qc7 7. Bd3 Nf6 8. Nd2 Bb7 9. O-O h5 10. Qf3 Ng4 11. g3 Ne5 12. Qe3 Bc5 { The g1-a7 diagonal is the downside of White's queenside fianchetto. } 13. c3 Nbc6 14. f4? { It is not wise to continue to open up the diagonal. I have long term pressure along the diagonals. } 14... Ng4 15. Qe2 b4 { Endless pressure on d4. } 16. Nf3 bxc3 17. Bxc3 Qb6 18. Qb2 e5 19. fxe5 Ngxe5 20. Bc4 Nxf3+ 21. Kg2 Ncxd4 { 0-1 Black wins. } { Ultimately too much pressure on that diagonal. Great illustration of the plan against 3. b3 } 0-1


