1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. Nc3 a6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Qc7 6. Bd3 Nc6 7. Nxc6 dxc6 8. O-O Nf6 9. f4 e5 10. Kh1 Bd6 11. f5 h5 12. a3 b5 { Simultaneously grabbing space on the kingside and queenside. } 13. Bg5 Bb7 14. Rf3 O-O-O { A logical move to bring the king to safety on the queenside and rook to the open d-file. Castling is very flexible in the Kan, especially the closed positions. The king can end up basically anywhere! } 15. Rh3 Ng4 16. Bxd8 Nf2+ 17. Kg1 Nxh3+ 18. gxh3 Rxd8 { White ends up with a damaged pawn structure in front of his king. } 19. Qxh5 g6 { Forcing open the g-file. } 20. Qf3 Rg8 21. Kh1 Bc5 22. b4 Bd4 23. Be2 c5 24. Rd1 Bxc3 { Otherwise, white plays Nd5 to shut down the Bb7. } 25. Qxc3 Bxe4+ 26. Bf3 Qc6 27. Rf1 gxf5 28. Qe3 Bxf3+ 29. Rxf3 f4 30. Qe2 c4 31. Qd1 Qe4 32. Qf1 f5 { 0-1 Black wins. } { White is basically paralyzed, and black's passed pawns just roll up the board at once. } 0-1


